text.description: An exceptional modern 'eco-home', boasting circa 3,251sqft of internal space, including a cinema room, benefitting from a South facing garden and two terraces, positioned next to Highbury Barn. Accommodation is immaculately presented comprising; a secure entrance, providing access to a vast entrance hallway on the ground floor, with plenty of storage, a cloak room and W.C, along with the kitchen/dining space to the rear which provides access to the tranquil South facing rear garden. There is a cinema room and large home office on the lower level, with the separate reception space housed on the first floor, as well as a bedroom with en-suite. A further two double bedrooms, both with en-suites are on the second floor, with the oversized principal suite with two terraces, (one front and one rear) and the fabulous bathroom on the top floor. The property is supremely well placed for the greenery and amenities of Highbury Fields, the shops of Highbury Barn including the renowned Godfreys butchers, fishmongers and Da Marios delicatessen. Transport can be found via a short walk to Highbury & Islington station (National Rail, Victoria Line & London Overground), along with Arsenal Underground (Piccadilly Line). The renowned restaurants of Farang, Westerns Laundry &  Primeur restaurant can be found locally within Highbury, they are certainly must trys!
